.Dd June 30, 2022
.Dt VOP_STRATEGY 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm VOP_STRATEGY
.Nd read or write a file system buffer
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/param.h
.In sys/buf.h
.In sys/vnode.h
.Ft int
.Fn VOP_STRATEGY "struct vnode *vp" "struct buf *bp"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The arguments are:
.Bl -tag -width 2n
.It Fa vp
The vnode that the buffer is for.
.It Fa bp
The buffer to be read or written.
.El
.Pp
This call either reads or writes data from a file, depending on the value of
.Fa bp->b_iocmd .
.Pp
The call may block.
.Sh RETURN VALUES
Always zero.
Errors should be signalled by setting the
.Dv BIO_ERROR
bit in
.Fa bp->b_ioflags
and setting
.Fa bp->b_error
to the appropriate
.Va errno
value.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr errno 2 ,
.Xr buf 9 ,
.Xr vnode 9
